snippet.title: [FORTNITE FITNESS] Hip-Hop Dance Workout for Kids
snippet.description:
*Support the channel! = } https://teespring.com/stores/coach-meger-fitness-games
FORTNITE DANCE TABATA ((Hip-Hop Version)) by Coach Meger Fitness Tabatas. Great way to mix up elementary pe class with a dance activity to music that allows students to choose a finess activity / dance in a structured high intensity interval workout.


TABATA is a form of HIIT (High Intensity Interval Training) used by fitness programs ranging from elementary PE to professional athletes. snippet.title: Toddler Kids Fitness ACTIVITIES for Kids at HOME Exercise
snippet.description:
Move and play and learn a lot, Fitness with the RoboTots. 

Watch RoboTots for fun indoor activities for kids at home ages 2-8. Great for active toddlers at home, preschool, kindergarten movement songs and kids exercises perfect for home, homeschool activities or for indoor kids activities at school. 

Kids join RoboTots and start jumping around to this Summer Olympics Fitness Adventure. Try swimming, surfing and fun gymnastics movements. Indoor activities to keep kids active and busy! Fun imaginative play and ideas for kids indoor games. If your children like to move and jump or if they already do kids yoga, they will love RoboTots fitness adventures. 

Learn coordination, balance and build your child’s confidence. Watch your children get better each time they complete new moves. If your kids are shy in group classes, start with RoboTots. This is a great way to have fun and develop skills right in your own home.

15 fun and easy moves for your little kids! This fun summer sports workout will get your kids jumping and dancing. Watch the timer- Kids love to earn stars as they complete each exercise move for 15 seconds. This is a special episode to earn medals! Lots of fun music and graphics for kids to see. 

RoboTots creates Family Friendly Content for parents and educators. Kids can enjoy these fun videos while learning the importance of being active at a young age.

Your kids can have fun with these simple exercise moves. Great ideas for brain breaks at school and indoor activities for home or the classroom.
